question: Which Indian badminton player won the bronze medal in men's singles in the 2019 BWF World Championships?
explanation: B. Sai Praneeth is the Indian badminton player won the bronze medal in men's singles in the 2019 BWF World Championships. The 2019 BWF World Championships was a badminton tournament which was held from 19 to 25 August 2019 at St. Jakobshalle in Basel, Switzerland.
